Package net.objectzoo.events.impl

This package contains support classes that implement EventDelegates ready to be used.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Event0AsyncDelegate
    An Event0AsyncDelegate implements Action0Async as well as Event0Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event0Delegate interface.
    Event0Delegate
    An Event0Delegate implements Action0 as well as Event0 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action0 interface to all subscribers of the Event0 interface.
    Event2AsyncDelegate<T1,​T2>
    An Event2AsyncDelegate implements Action2Async as well as Event2Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action2Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event2Delegate interface.
    Event2Delegate<T1,​T2>
    An Event2Delegate implements Action2 as well as Event2 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action2 interface to all subscribers of the Event2 interface.
    Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,​T2,​T3>
    An Event3AsyncDelegate implements Action3Async as well as Event3Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action3Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event3Delegate interface.
    Event3Delegate<T1,​T2,​T3>
    An Event3Delegate implements Action3 as well as Event3 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action3 interface to all subscribers of the Event3 interface.
    Event4AsyncDelegate<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    An Event4AsyncDelegate implements Action4Async as well as Event4Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action4Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event4Delegate interface.
    Event4Delegate<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    An Event4Delegate implements Action4 as well as Event4 and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action4 interface to all subscribers of the Event4 interface.
    EventAsyncDelegate<T>
    An EventAsyncDelegate implements ActionAsync as well as EventDelegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the ActionAsync interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the EventDelegate interface.
    EventDelegate<T>
    An EventDelegate implements Action as well as Event and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action interface to all subscribers of the Event interface.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Event0AsyncAdapter
    The Event0AsyncAdapter is class that adapts an Event0Delegate to Event0AsyncDelegate so that the original delegates subscribers can be invoked asynchronously.
    Event0Caller
    The Event0Caller is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to a single subscriber.
    Event0Distributor
    The Event0Distributor is a Event0Delegate implementation that allows event distribution to multiple subscribers.
